                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/800: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chase</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-30T15:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 2, 7.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tinoco called extraordinary session of Congress to meet August 1 for sundry
                    announced purposes. The regular session expires tomorrow. Yesterday the Congress
                    authorized Tinoco to make peace with Germany.</p>
                <p>Rumor circulated again that Tinoco will leave Costa Rica soon with Juan B. Quiros
                    to succeed him, and the Mexican Minister is to secure the approval of Julio
                    Acosta while in Nicaragua. Quiet for a few days, no new outrages reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
